	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm aware this might be a bit off subject, but concerning NES emulators with inaccurate sound...<br /><br />Does anyone ever have any problems with FCEUX? It's my emulator of choice, but sadly it faces a lot of crackling in it's audio while changing the focus of the window. Is anyone aware of how to fix these issues? I've tried altering everything from buffering to the output quality, but nothing seems to work. Oftentimes I'll mute the emulator entirely because of it's crackling.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


