	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES emulator(s) with inaccurate sound</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, the &quot;static&quot; in FCEUX during play is a result of odd synchronisation/timing issues pertaining to audio/video drivers and/or latency (regardless of what audio card I used (onboard Realtek or an Audigy SE)).  So it makes sense Vsync enable/disable would affect it.  Some of it has been fixed using FCEUX 2.2.3 SVN (I get binaries from emucr.com) and setting Vsync to &quot;Lazy Wait for Vblank&quot; and setting DirectDraw to &quot;No hardware acceleration&quot;.  I have similar synchronisation oddities in other emulators, which is mainly why I use Nestopia when actually wanting to play a NES/FC game, and FCEUX +other emulators solely for debugging/development.  That's just me though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


